routeIdea:
My idea is a route for "Route 66 Ghost Towns", which is real world.
The  pitch for this route is "Travel along the historic Route 66, exploring the ghost towns that were once bustling stops along this iconic highway. Experience the eerie silence and decaying remnants of a bygone era.".
Some ideas for steps are: 
	 - Chicago, Illinois to Pontiac, Illinois
	 - Pontiac, Illinois to Springfield, Illinois
	 - Springfield, Illinois to St. Louis, Missouri
	 - St. Louis, Missouri to Carthage, Missouri
	 - Carthage, Missouri to Santa Fe, New Mexico

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Begin your journey in Chicago, the starting point of the historic Route 66.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Arrive in Pontiac, known for its Route 66 Hall of Fame and Museum.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Follow Route 66 signs from Chicago to reach Pontiac.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Explore the Route 66 Hall of Fame and Museum in Pontiac.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Visit Springfield, the capital of Illinois, known for its Abraham Lincoln sites.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Continue on Route 66 south to reach Springfield.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Discover the Lincoln Home National Historic Site in Springfield.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Arrive in St. Louis, famous for its Gateway Arch and vibrant culture.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Follow Route 66 west to reach St. Louis.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Explore the Gateway Arch and other attractions in St. Louis.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Visit Carthage, known for its historic courthouse and Route 66 Drive-In Theatre.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Continue on Route 66 southwest to reach Carthage.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Enjoy the historic sites and Route 66 Drive-In Theatre in Carthage.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Arrive in Santa Fe, known for its Pueblo-style architecture and vibrant arts scene.
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Follow Route 66 through Oklahoma and Texas to reach Santa Fe.
